                    "company": "University of Twente",
                    "description": "During my PhD I focus on developing advanced magnetometers for the intra-operative detection of superparamagnetic nanoparticles in human tissue, for example during magnetic sentinel lymph node mapping in breast cancer diagnosis. I work with biomedical engineers, clinical technologists, surgeons and other professionals to develop this technology from the ground up and bring it to the clinic.\n\nThe use of these superparamagnetic nanoparticles and our detector allows replacement of the current radioisotope-based technique, which has many drawbacks, including radiation dose for patient and medical staff, high logistical burden for the clinic and limited availability.\n\nBy exploiting our knowledge of the behavior of these nanoparticles and bringing them to clinical practice, we aim to improve the quality and efficiency of existing medical procedures, from diagnostics to treatment in for example radiotherapy procedures. All this is carried out in tight communication with the end users to ensure efficient integration of our solutions in clinical practice.",
